      "name": "multipad_core_difference_degree_bound",
      "proof": [
        "\u039b_{C\u222aU} = \u039b_C \u039b_U and \u039b_{C'\u222aU} = \u039b_{C'} \u039b_U (disjoint unions).",
        "Phi_w equal means the monic degree-j locators agree in coefficients of X^{j\u22121},\u2026,X^{j\u2212w}, so deg(\u039b_C \u039b_U \u2212 \u039b_{C'} \u039b_U) \u2264 j\u2212w\u22121.",
        "Factor: (\u039b_C \u2212 \u039b_{C'}) \u039b_U has degree deg(\u039b_C\u2212\u039b_{C'})+e.",
        "Hence deg(\u039b_C\u2212\u039b_{C'})+e \u2264 j\u2212w\u22121.",
        "e=w+1 \u21d2 deg(\u039b_C\u2212\u039b_{C'}) \u2264 j\u2212w\u22121\u2212(w+1) = j\u22122w\u22122."
      ],
      "statement": "Suppose C \u2260 C' are (j\u2212e)-subsets, U,V are disjoint e-subsets with e=w+1, \u039b_U\u2212\u039b_V = c \u2208 F_p^\u00d7, and Phi_w(C\u222aU)=Phi_w(C'\u222aU)  (hence also = Phi_w(C\u222aV)=Phi_w(C'\u222aV)). Then deg(\u039b_C \u2212 \u039b_{C'}) \u2264 j \u2212 2w \u2212 2.",
      "status": "PROVED"
    },
    "path_Mpad1": {
      "name": "path_after_M_pad_one",
      "proof": [
        "v20 payment bridge + deployed t=e."
